	   <tr><td colspan=2>kiting as you refer to it is done mostly by druids & wizards, because they have the most powerful nukes/AE nukes. what you do is get a sow on yourself to make you run faster than the mobs, and then cast snare on the mob you wish to kite around, then just blast it to death with fast casting nukes while the mob is crawling to you.<br><br>while monks and other melee classes cant use this strategy, they can "reverse-kite" also known as "fear kiting"<br>just make sure you have a sow on (to run faster than the mobs as they run away from you, because some mobs run faster than PC's) and get a succesful ID on the mob, while they are running, smack em on the noggin.<br><br>this requires a lot of open space if you are fighting mobs that will aggro surrounding creatures when you fight them, or else you'll have a whole gang on you!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
